\begin_inset Caption Standard

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "fig:Beetle-tracks."

\end_inset

Results of radio-tracking coconut rhinoceros beetles at the Yigo and Asan
 release sites.
 Pushpin icons represent waypoints for tracked beetles (color code: red
 = beetle ended up in crown of tree; yellow: beetle ended up on or below
 the ground; orange: beetle was lost when it flew beyond the range of radio-trac
king receivers, orange lines are extrapolated tracks based on last observed
 bearing of radio signal).
 Circular icons represent pheromone traps (color code: cyan = barrel trap;
 orange = DeFence trap; red = bucket trap).
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\end_layout

\end_inset


